definitions.definition: To cause (someone or something) to be; to bring (someone or something) into existence ; to produce or initiate a person or thing.
To come into existence; to have origin or beginning; to spring , be derived ( from , with ).
examples: The scheme originated with the governor and council.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To cause (someone or something) to be; to bring (someone or something) into existence ; to produce or initiate a person or thing. [from 17th c.]
secondary_definitions: ( intransitive ) To come into existence; to have origin or beginning; to spring , be derived ( from , with ). [from 18th c.]
